23template<bool _ConjLhs, bool _ConjRhs>
24class gebp_traits<QInt8, QUInt8, _ConjLhs, _ConjRhs>

26public:
27 typedef QInt8 LhsScalar;
28 typedef QUInt8 RhsScalar;
29 typedef QInt32 ResScalar;

31 enum {
32 // Define register blocking scheme.
33 nr = 32,
34 mr = 32,
35 kr = 8,

37 LhsProgress = -1,
38 RhsProgress = -1
39 };

42// Specialized blocking for quantized implementations.
43// Used by TensorContractionThreadPool, inputs must have dimensions that are
44// multiples of 32.
45template<typename Index,
46 typename LeftTensor,
47 typename left_nocontract_t, typename left_contract_t,
48 bool left_inner_dim_contiguous, bool left_inner_dim_reordered, int LeftAlignment,
49 typename RightTensor,
50 typename right_nocontract_t, typename right_contract_t,
51 bool right_inner_dim_contiguous, bool right_inner_dim_reordered, int RightAlignment, int ShardingType>
52class TensorContractionBlocking<TensorContractionInputMapper<QInt8, Index, Lhs, LeftTensor, left_nocontract_t, left_contract_t, 32, left_inner_dim_contiguous, left_inner_dim_reordered, LeftAlignment>, TensorContractionInputMapper<QUInt8, Index, Rhs, RightTensor, right_nocontract_t, right_contract_t, 32, right_inner_dim_contiguous, right_inner_dim_reordered, RightAlignment>, Index, ShardingType> {
53 public:
54
55 typedef QInt8 LhsScalar;
56 typedef QUInt8 RhsScalar;
57
58 TensorContractionBlocking(Index k, Index m, Index n, Index num_threads = 1) :
59 kc_(k), mc_(m), nc_(n)
60 {
61 eigen_assert(m % 32 == 0);
62 eigen_assert(k % 32 == 0);
63 if (!k || !m || !n) {
64 return;
65 }
66
67 if (ShardingType == ShardByCol) {
68 eigen_assert(n % 32 == 0);
69 nc_ = (((n / num_threads) + 31) / 32) * 32;
70 }
71 else {
72 eigen_assert(n % 32 == 0 || n == 1);
73 // Special case to avoid breaking the unimplemented matrix-vector case
74 if (n == 1) {
75 nc_ = 32;
76 }
77 mc_ = (((m / num_threads) + 31) / 32) * 32;
78 }
79 }
80
81 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE Index kc() const { return kc_; }
82 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE Index mc() const { return mc_; }
83 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE Index nc() const { return nc_; }
84
85 private:
86 Index kc_;
87 Index mc_;
88 Index nc_;
89};

91// Specialized blocking for quantized implementations.
92// Used by TensorContraction and GeneralMatrixMatrix, inputs are padded to
93// multiples of 32.
94template <int MaxRows, int MaxCols, int MaxDepth, int KcFactor>
95class gemm_blocking_space<ColMajor, QInt8, QInt8, MaxRows, MaxCols, MaxDepth,
96 KcFactor, false>
97 : public level3_blocking<QInt8, QInt8> {
98 DenseIndex m_sizeA;
99 DenseIndex m_sizeB;
100
101 public:
102 gemm_blocking_space(DenseIndex rows, DenseIndex cols, DenseIndex depth,
103 DenseIndex /*num_threads*/, bool /*l3_blocking*/) {
104 this->m_mc = ((rows + 31) / 32) * 32;
105 this->m_nc = ((cols + 31) / 32) * 32;
106 this->m_kc = ((depth + 31) / 32) * 32;
107 m_sizeA = this->m_mc * this->m_kc;
108 m_sizeB = this->m_kc * this->m_nc;
109 }
110 void allocateA() {
111 if (this->m_blockA == 0) this->m_blockA = aligned_new<QInt8>(m_sizeA);
112 }
113 void allocateB() {
114 if (this->m_blockB == 0) this->m_blockB = aligned_new<QInt8>(m_sizeB);
115 }
116 void allocateAll() {
117 allocateA();
118 allocateB();
119 }
120 ~gemm_blocking_space() {
121 aligned_delete(this->m_blockA, m_sizeA);
122 aligned_delete(this->m_blockB, m_sizeB);
123 }
124};

189// Alternate implementations for any input sizes
190template <typename Index, typename DataMapper, int Pack1, int Pack2, bool Conjugate, bool PanelMode>
191EIGEN_DONT_INLINE void gemm_pack_lhs_any<QInt8, Index, DataMapper, Pack1, Pack2, ColMajor, Conjugate, PanelMode>::
192operator()(QInt8* blockA, const DataMapper& lhs, Index depth, Index rows, Index stride, Index offset) {
193 eigen_assert(stride == 0);
194 eigen_assert(offset == 0);
195
196 // Get vector pointer
197 __m256i* blockA_256 = reinterpret_cast<__m256i*>(blockA);
198
199 // Get even multiples of the dimensions
200 Index rows_32 = (rows / 32) * 32;
201 Index depth_8 = (depth / 8) * 8;
202
203 // Get padding for when depth is not a multiple of 32
204 int padding = 0;
205 if (depth % 32 != 0) {
206 int depth_32 = (depth / 32) * 32;
207 int extra_depth = depth - depth_32;
208 int extra_depth_8 = ((extra_depth + 7) / 8) * 8;
209 padding = 32 - extra_depth_8;
210 }
211
212 // Pack rows in sets of 32
213 for (Index m = 0; m < rows_32; m += 32) {
214 // Pack depth in sets of 8
215 for (Index k = 0; k < depth_8; k += 8) {
216 // Load vectors
217 __m256i L_A = lhs.loadPacket(m, k);
218 __m256i L_B = lhs.loadPacket(m, k + 1);
219
220 // Interleave 8-bit elements
221 __m256i L_AB0_AB16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi8(L_A, L_B);
222 __m256i L_AB8_AB24 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi8(L_A, L_B);
223
224 __m256i L_C = lhs.loadPacket(m, k + 2);
225 __m256i L_D = lhs.loadPacket(m, k + 3);
226 __m256i L_CD0_CD16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi8(L_C, L_D);
227 __m256i L_CD8_CD24 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi8(L_C, L_D);
228
229 // Interleave 16-bit elements
230 __m256i L_AD0_AD16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi16(L_AB0_AB16, L_CD0_CD16);
231 __m256i L_AD4_AD20 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi16(L_AB0_AB16, L_CD0_CD16);
232
233 // Use permute before we store to cross 128-bit lanes
234 __m256i L_AD0 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_AD0_AD16, L_AD4_AD20, 0x20);
235 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_AD0);
236
237 // Complete packing for 32 x 8 block
238 __m256i L_AD16 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_AD0_AD16, L_AD4_AD20, 0x31);
239 __m256i L_AD8_AD24 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi16(L_AB8_AB24, L_CD8_CD24);
240 __m256i L_AD12_AD28 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi16(L_AB8_AB24, L_CD8_CD24);
241 __m256i L_AD8 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_AD8_AD24, L_AD12_AD28, 0x20);
242 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_AD8);
243 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_AD16);
244 __m256i L_AD24 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_AD8_AD24, L_AD12_AD28, 0x31);
245 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_AD24);
246 __m256i L_E = lhs.loadPacket(m, k + 4);
247 __m256i L_F = lhs.loadPacket(m, k + 5);
248 __m256i L_EF0_EF16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi8(L_E, L_F);
249 __m256i L_EF8_EF24 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi8(L_E, L_F);
250 __m256i L_G = lhs.loadPacket(m, k + 6);
251 __m256i L_H = lhs.loadPacket(m, k + 7);
252 __m256i L_GH0_GH16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi8(L_G, L_H);
253 __m256i L_GH8_GH24 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi8(L_G, L_H);
254 __m256i L_EH0_EH16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi16(L_EF0_EF16, L_GH0_GH16);
255 __m256i L_EH4_EH20 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi16(L_EF0_EF16, L_GH0_GH16);
256 __m256i L_EH0 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_EH0_EH16, L_EH4_EH20, 0x20);
257 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_EH0);
258 __m256i L_EH16 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_EH0_EH16, L_EH4_EH20, 0x31);
259 __m256i L_EH8_EH24 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi16(L_EF8_EF24, L_GH8_GH24);
260 __m256i L_EH12_EH28 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi16(L_EF8_EF24, L_GH8_GH24);
261 __m256i L_EH8 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_EH8_EH24, L_EH12_EH28, 0x20);
262 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_EH8);
263 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_EH16);
264 __m256i L_EH24 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_EH8_EH24, L_EH12_EH28, 0x31);
265 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_EH24);
266 }
267
268 // Finish the k dimension, padding with zeros
269 if (depth_8 < depth) {
270 __m256i L_A, L_B, L_C, L_D, L_E, L_F, L_G, L_H;
271 switch (depth - depth_8) {
272 case 1:
273 L_A = lhs.loadPacket(m, depth_8);
274 L_B = _mm256_setzero_si256();
275 L_C = _mm256_setzero_si256();
276 L_D = _mm256_setzero_si256();
277 L_E = _mm256_setzero_si256();
278 L_F = _mm256_setzero_si256();
279 L_G = _mm256_setzero_si256();
280 L_H = _mm256_setzero_si256();
281 break;
282 case 2:
283 L_A = lhs.loadPacket(m, depth_8);
284 L_B = lhs.loadPacket(m, depth_8 + 1);
285 L_C = _mm256_setzero_si256();
286 L_D = _mm256_setzero_si256();
287 L_E = _mm256_setzero_si256();
288 L_F = _mm256_setzero_si256();
289 L_G = _mm256_setzero_si256();
290 L_H = _mm256_setzero_si256();
291 break;
292 case 3:
293 L_A = lhs.loadPacket(m, depth_8);
294 L_B = lhs.loadPacket(m, depth_8 + 1);
295 L_C = lhs.loadPacket(m, depth_8 + 2);
296 L_D = _mm256_setzero_si256();
297 L_E = _mm256_setzero_si256();
298 L_F = _mm256_setzero_si256();
299 L_G = _mm256_setzero_si256();
300 L_H = _mm256_setzero_si256();
301 break;
302 case 4:
303 L_A = lhs.loadPacket(m, depth_8);
304 L_B = lhs.loadPacket(m, depth_8 + 1);
305 L_C = lhs.loadPacket(m, depth_8 + 2);
306 L_D = lhs.loadPacket(m, depth_8 + 3);
307 L_E = _mm256_setzero_si256();
308 L_F = _mm256_setzero_si256();
309 L_G = _mm256_setzero_si256();
310 L_H = _mm256_setzero_si256();
311 break;
312 case 5:
313 L_A = lhs.loadPacket(m, depth_8);
314 L_B = lhs.loadPacket(m, depth_8 + 1);
315 L_C = lhs.loadPacket(m, depth_8 + 2);
316 L_D = lhs.loadPacket(m, depth_8 + 3);
317 L_E = lhs.loadPacket(m, depth_8 + 4);
318 L_F = _mm256_setzero_si256();
319 L_G = _mm256_setzero_si256();
320 L_H = _mm256_setzero_si256();
321 break;
322 case 6:
323 L_A = lhs.loadPacket(m, depth_8);
324 L_B = lhs.loadPacket(m, depth_8 + 1);
325 L_C = lhs.loadPacket(m, depth_8 + 2);
326 L_D = lhs.loadPacket(m, depth_8 + 3);
327 L_E = lhs.loadPacket(m, depth_8 + 4);
328 L_F = lhs.loadPacket(m, depth_8 + 5);
329 L_G = _mm256_setzero_si256();
330 L_H = _mm256_setzero_si256();
331 break;
332 case 7:
333 L_A = lhs.loadPacket(m, depth_8);
334 L_B = lhs.loadPacket(m, depth_8 + 1);
335 L_C = lhs.loadPacket(m, depth_8 + 2);
336 L_D = lhs.loadPacket(m, depth_8 + 3);
337 L_E = lhs.loadPacket(m, depth_8 + 4);
338 L_F = lhs.loadPacket(m, depth_8 + 5);
339 L_G = lhs.loadPacket(m, depth_8 + 6);
340 L_H = _mm256_setzero_si256();
341 break;
342 }
343
344 // Interleave 8-bit elements
345 __m256i L_AB0_AB16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi8(L_A, L_B);
346 __m256i L_AB8_AB24 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi8(L_A, L_B);
347
348 __m256i L_CD0_CD16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi8(L_C, L_D);
349 __m256i L_CD8_CD24 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi8(L_C, L_D);
350
351 // Interleave 16-bit elements
352 __m256i L_AD0_AD16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi16(L_AB0_AB16, L_CD0_CD16);
353 __m256i L_AD4_AD20 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi16(L_AB0_AB16, L_CD0_CD16);
354
355 // Use permute before we store to cross 128-bit lanes
356 __m256i L_AD0 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_AD0_AD16, L_AD4_AD20, 0x20);
357 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_AD0);
358
359 // Complete packing
360 __m256i L_AD16 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_AD0_AD16, L_AD4_AD20, 0x31);
361 __m256i L_AD8_AD24 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi16(L_AB8_AB24, L_CD8_CD24);
362 __m256i L_AD12_AD28 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi16(L_AB8_AB24, L_CD8_CD24);
363 __m256i L_AD8 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_AD8_AD24, L_AD12_AD28, 0x20);
364 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_AD8);
365 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_AD16);
366 __m256i L_AD24 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_AD8_AD24, L_AD12_AD28, 0x31);
367 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_AD24);
368 __m256i L_EF0_EF16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi8(L_E, L_F);
369 __m256i L_EF8_EF24 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi8(L_E, L_F);
370 __m256i L_GH0_GH16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi8(L_G, L_H);
371 __m256i L_GH8_GH24 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi8(L_G, L_H);
372 __m256i L_EH0_EH16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi16(L_EF0_EF16, L_GH0_GH16);
373 __m256i L_EH4_EH20 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi16(L_EF0_EF16, L_GH0_GH16);
374 __m256i L_EH0 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_EH0_EH16, L_EH4_EH20, 0x20);
375 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_EH0);
376 __m256i L_EH16 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_EH0_EH16, L_EH4_EH20, 0x31);
377 __m256i L_EH8_EH24 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi16(L_EF8_EF24, L_GH8_GH24);
378 __m256i L_EH12_EH28 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi16(L_EF8_EF24, L_GH8_GH24);
379 __m256i L_EH8 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_EH8_EH24, L_EH12_EH28, 0x20);
380 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_EH8);
381 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_EH16);
382 __m256i L_EH24 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_EH8_EH24, L_EH12_EH28, 0x31);
383 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_EH24);
384 }
385 blockA_256 += padding;
386 }
387
388 // Finish the m dimension, padding with zeros
389 if (rows_32 < rows) {
390 // Pack depth in sets of 8
391 for (Index k = 0; k < depth_8; k += 8) {
392 // Load vectors
393 __m256i L_A = _mm256_setzero_si256();
394 __m256i L_B = _mm256_setzero_si256();
395 __m256i L_C = _mm256_setzero_si256();
396 __m256i L_D = _mm256_setzero_si256();
397 __m256i L_E = _mm256_setzero_si256();
398 __m256i L_F = _mm256_setzero_si256();
399 __m256i L_G = _mm256_setzero_si256();
400 __m256i L_H = _mm256_setzero_si256();
401 for (Index m = 0; m < rows - rows_32; m++) {
402 QInt8* ptr = (QInt8*) &L_A;
403 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, k);
404 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_B;
405 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, k + 1);
406 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_C;
407 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, k + 2);
408 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_D;
409 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, k + 3);
410 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_E;
411 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, k + 4);
412 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_F;
413 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, k + 5);
414 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_G;
415 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, k + 6);
416 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_H;
417 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, k + 7);
418 }
419
420 // Interleave 8-bit elements
421 __m256i L_AB0_AB16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi8(L_A, L_B);
422 __m256i L_AB8_AB24 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi8(L_A, L_B);
423 __m256i L_CD0_CD16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi8(L_C, L_D);
424 __m256i L_CD8_CD24 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi8(L_C, L_D);
425
426 // Interleave 16-bit elements
427 __m256i L_AD0_AD16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi16(L_AB0_AB16, L_CD0_CD16);
428 __m256i L_AD4_AD20 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi16(L_AB0_AB16, L_CD0_CD16);
429
430 // Use permute before we store to cross 128-bit lanes
431 __m256i L_AD0 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_AD0_AD16, L_AD4_AD20, 0x20);
432 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_AD0);
433
434 // Complete packing for 32 x 8 block
435 __m256i L_AD16 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_AD0_AD16, L_AD4_AD20, 0x31);
436 __m256i L_AD8_AD24 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi16(L_AB8_AB24, L_CD8_CD24);
437 __m256i L_AD12_AD28 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi16(L_AB8_AB24, L_CD8_CD24);
438 __m256i L_AD8 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_AD8_AD24, L_AD12_AD28, 0x20);
439 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_AD8);
440 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_AD16);
441 __m256i L_AD24 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_AD8_AD24, L_AD12_AD28, 0x31);
442 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_AD24);
443 __m256i L_EF0_EF16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi8(L_E, L_F);
444 __m256i L_EF8_EF24 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi8(L_E, L_F);
445 __m256i L_GH0_GH16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi8(L_G, L_H);
446 __m256i L_GH8_GH24 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi8(L_G, L_H);
447 __m256i L_EH0_EH16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi16(L_EF0_EF16, L_GH0_GH16);
448 __m256i L_EH4_EH20 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi16(L_EF0_EF16, L_GH0_GH16);
449 __m256i L_EH0 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_EH0_EH16, L_EH4_EH20, 0x20);
450 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_EH0);
451 __m256i L_EH16 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_EH0_EH16, L_EH4_EH20, 0x31);
452 __m256i L_EH8_EH24 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi16(L_EF8_EF24, L_GH8_GH24);
453 __m256i L_EH12_EH28 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi16(L_EF8_EF24, L_GH8_GH24);
454 __m256i L_EH8 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_EH8_EH24, L_EH12_EH28, 0x20);
455 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_EH8);
456 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_EH16);
457 __m256i L_EH24 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_EH8_EH24, L_EH12_EH28, 0x31);
458 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_EH24);
459 }
460
461 // Finish the k dimension, padding with zeros
462 if (depth_8 < depth) {
463 __m256i L_A, L_B, L_C, L_D, L_E, L_F, L_G, L_H;
464 QInt8* ptr;
465 switch (depth - depth_8) {
466 case 1:
467 L_A = _mm256_setzero_si256();
468 L_B = _mm256_setzero_si256();
469 L_C = _mm256_setzero_si256();
470 L_D = _mm256_setzero_si256();
471 L_E = _mm256_setzero_si256();
472 L_F = _mm256_setzero_si256();
473 L_G = _mm256_setzero_si256();
474 L_H = _mm256_setzero_si256();
475 for (Index m = 0; m < rows - rows_32; m++) {
476 QInt8* ptr = (QInt8*) &L_A;
477 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, depth_8);
478 }
479 break;
480 case 2:
481 L_A = _mm256_setzero_si256();
482 L_B = _mm256_setzero_si256();
483 L_C = _mm256_setzero_si256();
484 L_D = _mm256_setzero_si256();
485 L_E = _mm256_setzero_si256();
486 L_F = _mm256_setzero_si256();
487 L_G = _mm256_setzero_si256();
488 L_H = _mm256_setzero_si256();
489 for (Index m = 0; m < rows - rows_32; m++) {
490 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_A;
491 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, depth_8);
492 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_B;
493 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, depth_8 + 1);
494 }
495 break;
496 case 3:
497 L_A = _mm256_setzero_si256();
498 L_B = _mm256_setzero_si256();
499 L_C = _mm256_setzero_si256();
500 L_D = _mm256_setzero_si256();
501 L_E = _mm256_setzero_si256();
502 L_F = _mm256_setzero_si256();
503 L_G = _mm256_setzero_si256();
504 L_H = _mm256_setzero_si256();
505 for (Index m = 0; m < rows - rows_32; m++) {
506 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_A;
507 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, depth_8);
508 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_B;
509 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, depth_8 + 1);
510 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_C;
511 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, depth_8 + 2);
512 }
513 break;
514 case 4:
515 L_A = _mm256_setzero_si256();
516 L_B = _mm256_setzero_si256();
517 L_C = _mm256_setzero_si256();
518 L_D = _mm256_setzero_si256();
519 L_E = _mm256_setzero_si256();
520 L_F = _mm256_setzero_si256();
521 L_G = _mm256_setzero_si256();
522 L_H = _mm256_setzero_si256();
523 for (Index m = 0; m < rows - rows_32; m++) {
524 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_A;
525 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, depth_8);
526 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_B;
527 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, depth_8 + 1);
528 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_C;
529 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, depth_8 + 2);
530 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_D;
531 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, depth_8 + 3);
532 }
533 break;
534 case 5:
535 L_A = _mm256_setzero_si256();
536 L_B = _mm256_setzero_si256();
537 L_C = _mm256_setzero_si256();
538 L_D = _mm256_setzero_si256();
539 L_E = _mm256_setzero_si256();
540 L_F = _mm256_setzero_si256();
541 L_G = _mm256_setzero_si256();
542 L_H = _mm256_setzero_si256();
543 for (Index m = 0; m < rows - rows_32; m++) {
544 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_A;
545 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, depth_8);
546 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_B;
547 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, depth_8 + 1);
548 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_C;
549 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, depth_8 + 2);
550 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_D;
551 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, depth_8 + 3);
552 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_E;
553 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, depth_8 + 4);
554 }
555 break;
556 case 6:
557 L_A = _mm256_setzero_si256();
558 L_B = _mm256_setzero_si256();
559 L_C = _mm256_setzero_si256();
560 L_D = _mm256_setzero_si256();
561 L_E = _mm256_setzero_si256();
562 L_F = _mm256_setzero_si256();
563 L_G = _mm256_setzero_si256();
564 L_H = _mm256_setzero_si256();
565 for (Index m = 0; m < rows - rows_32; m++) {
566 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_A;
567 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, depth_8);
568 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_B;
569 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, depth_8 + 1);
570 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_C;
571 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, depth_8 + 2);
572 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_D;
573 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, depth_8 + 3);
574 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_E;
575 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, depth_8 + 4);
576 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_F;
577 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, depth_8 + 5);
578 }
579 break;
580 case 7:
581 L_A = _mm256_setzero_si256();
582 L_B = _mm256_setzero_si256();
583 L_C = _mm256_setzero_si256();
584 L_D = _mm256_setzero_si256();
585 L_E = _mm256_setzero_si256();
586 L_F = _mm256_setzero_si256();
587 L_G = _mm256_setzero_si256();
588 L_H = _mm256_setzero_si256();
589 for (Index m = 0; m < rows - rows_32; m++) {
590 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_A;
591 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, depth_8);
592 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_B;
593 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, depth_8 + 1);
594 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_C;
595 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, depth_8 + 2);
596 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_D;
597 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, depth_8 + 3);
598 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_E;
599 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, depth_8 + 4);
600 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_F;
601 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, depth_8 + 5);
602 ptr = (QInt8*) &L_G;
603 ptr[m] = lhs(rows_32 + m, depth_8 + 6);
604 }
605 break;
606 }
607
608 // Interleave 8-bit elements
609 __m256i L_AB0_AB16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi8(L_A, L_B);
610 __m256i L_AB8_AB24 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi8(L_A, L_B);
611 __m256i L_CD0_CD16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi8(L_C, L_D);
612 __m256i L_CD8_CD24 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi8(L_C, L_D);
613
614 // Interleave 16-bit elements
615 __m256i L_AD0_AD16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi16(L_AB0_AB16, L_CD0_CD16);
616 __m256i L_AD4_AD20 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi16(L_AB0_AB16, L_CD0_CD16);
617
618 // Use permute before we store to cross 128-bit lanes
619 __m256i L_AD0 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_AD0_AD16, L_AD4_AD20, 0x20);
620 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_AD0);
621
622 // Complete packing
623 __m256i L_AD16 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_AD0_AD16, L_AD4_AD20, 0x31);
624 __m256i L_AD8_AD24 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi16(L_AB8_AB24, L_CD8_CD24);
625 __m256i L_AD12_AD28 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi16(L_AB8_AB24, L_CD8_CD24);
626 __m256i L_AD8 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_AD8_AD24, L_AD12_AD28, 0x20);
627 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_AD8);
628 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_AD16);
629 __m256i L_AD24 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_AD8_AD24, L_AD12_AD28, 0x31);
630 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_AD24);
631 __m256i L_EF0_EF16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi8(L_E, L_F);
632 __m256i L_EF8_EF24 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi8(L_E, L_F);
633 __m256i L_GH0_GH16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi8(L_G, L_H);
634 __m256i L_GH8_GH24 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi8(L_G, L_H);
635 __m256i L_EH0_EH16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi16(L_EF0_EF16, L_GH0_GH16);
636 __m256i L_EH4_EH20 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi16(L_EF0_EF16, L_GH0_GH16);
637 __m256i L_EH0 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_EH0_EH16, L_EH4_EH20, 0x20);
638 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_EH0);
639 __m256i L_EH16 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_EH0_EH16, L_EH4_EH20, 0x31);
640 __m256i L_EH8_EH24 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi16(L_EF8_EF24, L_GH8_GH24);
641 __m256i L_EH12_EH28 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi16(L_EF8_EF24, L_GH8_GH24);
642 __m256i L_EH8 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_EH8_EH24, L_EH12_EH28, 0x20);
643 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_EH8);
644 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_EH16);
645 __m256i L_EH24 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_EH8_EH24, L_EH12_EH28, 0x31);
646 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_EH24);
647 }
648 }
649}

651template <typename Index, typename DataMapper, int nr, bool Conjugate, bool PanelMode>
652EIGEN_DONT_INLINE void gemm_pack_rhs_any<QUInt8, Index, DataMapper, nr, ColMajor, Conjugate, PanelMode>::
653operator()(QUInt8* blockB, const DataMapper& rhs, Index depth, Index cols, Index stride, Index offset) {
654 eigen_assert(stride == 0);
655 eigen_assert(offset == 0);
656
657 // Get vector pointer
658 __m256i* blockB_256 = reinterpret_cast<__m256i*>(blockB);
659
660 // Get even multiples of the dimensions
661 Index cols_32 = (cols / 32) * 32;
662 Index depth_32 = (depth / 32) * 32;
663
664 // Perform a step of the packing for 4 columns
665 __m256i R_AB_L, R_AB_H, R_CD_L, R_CD_H, R_AD_0, R_AD_8, R_AD_16, R_AD_24;
666#define PACK_STEP \
667 R_AB_L = _mm256_unpacklo_epi64(R_A, R_B); \
668 R_CD_L = _mm256_unpacklo_epi64(R_C, R_D); \
669 R_AB_H = _mm256_unpackhi_epi64(R_A, R_B); \
670 R_CD_H = _mm256_unpackhi_epi64(R_C, R_D); \
671 R_AD_0 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(R_AB_L, R_CD_L, 0x20); \
672 R_AD_16 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(R_AB_L, R_CD_L, 0x31); \
673 R_AD_8 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(R_AB_H, R_CD_H, 0x20); \
674 R_AD_24 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(R_AB_H, R_CD_H, 0x31); \
675 _mm256_store_si256(blockB_256, R_AD_0); \
676 _mm256_store_si256(blockB_256 + 8, R_AD_8); \
677 _mm256_store_si256(blockB_256 + 16, R_AD_16); \
678 _mm256_store_si256(blockB_256 + 24, R_AD_24); \
679 blockB_256++;
680
681 // Pack cols in sets of 32
682 for (Index n = 0; n < cols_32; n += 32) {
683 // Pack depth in sets of 32
684 for (Index k = 0; k < depth_32; k += 32) {
685 __m256i R_A = rhs.loadPacket(k, n);
686 __m256i R_B = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 1);
687 __m256i R_C = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 2);
688 __m256i R_D = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 3);
689 PACK_STEP;
690
691 R_A = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 4);
692 R_B = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 5);
693 R_C = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 6);
694 R_D = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 7);
695 PACK_STEP;
696
697 R_A = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 8);
698 R_B = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 9);
699 R_C = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 10);
700 R_D = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 11);
701 PACK_STEP;
702
703 R_A = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 12);
704 R_B = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 13);
705 R_C = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 14);
706 R_D = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 15);
707 PACK_STEP;
708
709 R_A = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 16);
710 R_B = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 17);
711 R_C = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 18);
712 R_D = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 19);
713 PACK_STEP;
714
715 R_A = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 20);
716 R_B = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 21);
717 R_C = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 22);
718 R_D = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 23);
719 PACK_STEP;
720
721 R_A = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 24);
722 R_B = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 25);
723 R_C = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 26);
724 R_D = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 27);
725 PACK_STEP;
726
727 R_A = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 28);
728 R_B = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 29);
729 R_C = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 30);
730 R_D = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 31);
731 PACK_STEP;
732
733 blockB_256 += 24;
734 }
735
736 if (depth_32 < depth) {
737 QUInt8* ptr;
738 __m256i R_A = _mm256_setzero_si256();
739 __m256i R_B = _mm256_setzero_si256();
740 __m256i R_C = _mm256_setzero_si256();
741 __m256i R_D = _mm256_setzero_si256();
742 for (Index k = depth_32; k < depth; k++) {
743 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_A;
744 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n);
745 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_B;
746 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 1);
747 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_C;
748 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 2);
749 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_D;
750 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 3);
751 }
752 PACK_STEP;
753
754 R_A = _mm256_setzero_si256();
755 R_B = _mm256_setzero_si256();
756 R_C = _mm256_setzero_si256();
757 R_D = _mm256_setzero_si256();
758 for (Index k = depth_32; k < depth; k++) {
759 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_A;
760 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 4);
761 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_B;
762 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 5);
763 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_C;
764 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 6);
765 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_D;
766 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 7);
767 }
768 PACK_STEP;
769
770 R_A = _mm256_setzero_si256();
771 R_B = _mm256_setzero_si256();
772 R_C = _mm256_setzero_si256();
773 R_D = _mm256_setzero_si256();
774 for (Index k = depth_32; k < depth; k++) {
775 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_A;
776 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 8);
777 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_B;
778 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 9);
779 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_C;
780 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 10);
781 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_D;
782 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 11);
783 }
784 PACK_STEP;
785
786 R_A = _mm256_setzero_si256();
787 R_B = _mm256_setzero_si256();
788 R_C = _mm256_setzero_si256();
789 R_D = _mm256_setzero_si256();
790 for (Index k = depth_32; k < depth; k++) {
791 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_A;
792 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 12);
793 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_B;
794 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 13);
795 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_C;
796 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 14);
797 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_D;
798 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 15);
799 }
800 PACK_STEP;
801
802 R_A = _mm256_setzero_si256();
803 R_B = _mm256_setzero_si256();
804 R_C = _mm256_setzero_si256();
805 R_D = _mm256_setzero_si256();
806 for (Index k = depth_32; k < depth; k++) {
807 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_A;
808 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 16);
809 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_B;
810 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 17);
811 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_C;
812 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 18);
813 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_D;
814 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 19);
815 }
816 PACK_STEP;
817
818 R_A = _mm256_setzero_si256();
819 R_B = _mm256_setzero_si256();
820 R_C = _mm256_setzero_si256();
821 R_D = _mm256_setzero_si256();
822 for (Index k = depth_32; k < depth; k++) {
823 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_A;
824 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 20);
825 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_B;
826 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 21);
827 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_C;
828 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 22);
829 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_D;
830 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 23);
831 }
832 PACK_STEP;
833
834 R_A = _mm256_setzero_si256();
835 R_B = _mm256_setzero_si256();
836 R_C = _mm256_setzero_si256();
837 R_D = _mm256_setzero_si256();
838 for (Index k = depth_32; k < depth; k++) {
839 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_A;
840 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 24);
841 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_B;
842 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 25);
843 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_C;
844 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 26);
845 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_D;
846 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 27);
847 }
848 PACK_STEP;
849
850 R_A = _mm256_setzero_si256();
851 R_B = _mm256_setzero_si256();
852 R_C = _mm256_setzero_si256();
853 R_D = _mm256_setzero_si256();
854 for (Index k = depth_32; k < depth; k++) {
855 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_A;
856 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 28);
857 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_B;
858 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 29);
859 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_C;
860 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 30);
861 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_D;
862 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 31);
863 }
864 PACK_STEP;
865 blockB_256 += 24;
866 }
867 }
868
869 // Finish packing cols
870 if (cols_32 < cols) {
871 // Pack depth in sets of 32
872 for (Index k = 0; k < depth_32; k += 32) {
873 __m256i R_A, R_B, R_C, R_D;
874 Index n;
875 for (n = cols_32; n < cols; n += 4) {
876 switch (cols - n) {
877 case 1:
878 R_A = rhs.loadPacket(k, n);
879 R_B = _mm256_setzero_si256();
880 R_C = _mm256_setzero_si256();
881 R_D = _mm256_setzero_si256();
882 PACK_STEP;
883 break;
884 case 2:
885 R_A = rhs.loadPacket(k, n);
886 R_B = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 1);
887 R_C = _mm256_setzero_si256();
888 R_D = _mm256_setzero_si256();
889 PACK_STEP;
890 break;
891 case 3:
892 R_A = rhs.loadPacket(k, n);
893 R_B = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 1);
894 R_C = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 2);
895 R_D = _mm256_setzero_si256();
896 PACK_STEP;
897 break;
898 default:
899 R_A = rhs.loadPacket(k, n);
900 R_B = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 1);
901 R_C = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 2);
902 R_D = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 3);
903 PACK_STEP;
904 break;
905 }
906 }
907
908 // Increment the block pointer.
909 // We must pad if cols is not a multiple of 32.
910 blockB_256 += 32 - (n - cols_32) / 4;
911 }
912
913 if (depth_32 < depth) {
914 for (Index n = cols_32; n < cols; n += 4) {
915 QUInt8* ptr;
916 __m256i R_A = _mm256_setzero_si256();
917 __m256i R_B = _mm256_setzero_si256();
918 __m256i R_C = _mm256_setzero_si256();
919 __m256i R_D = _mm256_setzero_si256();
920 switch (cols - n) {
921 case 1:
922 for (Index k = depth_32; k < depth; k++) {
923 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_A;
924 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n);
925 }
926 PACK_STEP;
927 break;
928 case 2:
929 for (Index k = depth_32; k < depth; k++) {
930 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_A;
931 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n);
932 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_B;
933 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 1);
934 }
935 PACK_STEP;
936 break;
937 case 3:
938 for (Index k = depth_32; k < depth; k++) {
939 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_A;
940 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n);
941 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_B;
942 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 1);
943 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_C;
944 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 2);
945 }
946 PACK_STEP;
947 break;
948 default:
949 for (Index k = depth_32; k < depth; k++) {
950 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_A;
951 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n);
952 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_B;
953 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 1);
954 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_C;
955 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 2);
956 ptr = (QUInt8*) &R_D;
957 ptr[k - depth_32] = rhs(k, n + 3);
958 }
959 PACK_STEP;
960 break;
961 }
962 }
963 }
964 }
965#undef PACK_STEP
966}

1220 }
1221 }

1224 memset(blockO, 0, 32 * 32 * sizeof(QInt32));

1229// Below are the fully optimized versions that are correct only for sizes that
1230// are multiple of 32. It is about a 10% performance benefit to keep these
1231// implementations separate.
1232
1233// Arrange a block of the left input matrix in contiguous memory.
1234//
1235// Given column major input (A0 beside A1 in memory):
1236// A0 B0 C0 D0 E0 F0 G0 H0 ...
1237// A1 B1 C1 D1 E1 F1 G1 H1 ...
1238// A2 B2 C2 D2 E2 F2 G2 H2 ...
1239// A3 B3 C3 D3 E3 F3 G3 H3 ...
1240// A4 B4 C4 D4 E4 F4 G4 H4 ...
1241// A5 B5 C5 D5 E5 F5 G5 H5 ...
1242// A6 B6 C6 D6 E6 F6 G6 H6 ...
1243// A7 B7 C7 D7 E7 F7 G7 H7 ...
1244// A8 ...
1245// ...
1246//
1247// Packing yields output (A0 beside B0 in memory):
1248// A0 B0 C0 D0
1249// A1 B1 C1 D1
1250// A2 B2 C2 D2
1251// A3 B3 C3 D3
1252// A4 B4 C4 D4
1253// A5 B5 C5 D5
1254// A6 B6 C6 D6
1255// A7 B7 C7 D7
1256// ...
1257// A31 B31 C31 D31
1258// E0 F0 G0 H0
1259// E1 F1 G1 H1
1260// E2 F2 G2 H2
1261// E3 F3 G3 H3
1262// E4 F4 G4 H4
1263// E5 F5 G5 H5
1264// E6 F6 G6 H6
1265// E7 F7 G7 H7
1266// ...
1267//
1268// Four elements of the same row are arranged contiguously because maddubs and
1269// madd both perform an adjacent addition in the kernel.
1270template <typename Index, typename DataMapper, int Pack1, int Pack2,
1271 bool Conjugate, bool PanelMode>
1272struct gemm_pack_lhs<QInt8, Index, DataMapper, Pack1, Pack2, ColMajor,
1273 Conjugate, PanelMode> {
1274 EIGEN_DONT_INLINE void operator()(QInt8* blockA, const DataMapper& lhs,
1275 Index depth, Index rows, Index stride = 0,
1276 Index offset = 0);
1277};
1278
1279template <typename Index, typename DataMapper, int Pack1, int Pack2,
1280 bool Conjugate, bool PanelMode>
1281EIGEN_DONT_INLINE void gemm_pack_lhs<QInt8, Index, DataMapper, Pack1, Pack2,
1282 ColMajor, Conjugate, PanelMode>::
1283operator()(QInt8* blockA, const DataMapper& lhs, Index depth, Index rows,
1284 Index stride, Index offset) {
1285 eigen_assert(stride == 0);
1286 eigen_assert(offset == 0);
1287
1288 // Use alternate function for weird sizes
1289 if (rows % 32 != 0 || depth % 32 != 0) {
1290 gemm_pack_lhs_any<QInt8, Index, DataMapper, Pack1, Pack2, ColMajor, Conjugate, PanelMode> lhs_pack;
1291 return lhs_pack(blockA, lhs, depth, rows, stride, offset);
1292 }
1293
1294 // Get vector pointer
1295 __m256i* blockA_256 = reinterpret_cast<__m256i*>(blockA);
1296
1297 // Pack rows in sets of 32
1298 for (Index m = 0; m < rows; m += 32) {
1299 // Pack depth in sets of 8
1300 for (Index k = 0; k < depth; k += 8) {
1301 // Load vectors
1302 __m256i L_A = lhs.loadPacket(m, k);
1303 __m256i L_B = lhs.loadPacket(m, k + 1);
1304
1305 // Interleave 8-bit elements
1306 __m256i L_AB0_AB16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi8(L_A, L_B);
1307 __m256i L_AB8_AB24 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi8(L_A, L_B);
1308
1309 __m256i L_C = lhs.loadPacket(m, k + 2);
1310 __m256i L_D = lhs.loadPacket(m, k + 3);
1311 __m256i L_CD0_CD16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi8(L_C, L_D);
1312 __m256i L_CD8_CD24 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi8(L_C, L_D);
1313
1314 // Interleave 16-bit elements
1315 __m256i L_AD0_AD16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi16(L_AB0_AB16, L_CD0_CD16);
1316 __m256i L_AD4_AD20 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi16(L_AB0_AB16, L_CD0_CD16);
1317
1318 // Use permute before we store to cross 128-bit lanes
1319 __m256i L_AD0 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_AD0_AD16, L_AD4_AD20, 0x20);
1320 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_AD0);
1321
1322 // Complete packing for 32 x 8 block
1323 __m256i L_AD16 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_AD0_AD16, L_AD4_AD20, 0x31);
1324 __m256i L_AD8_AD24 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi16(L_AB8_AB24, L_CD8_CD24);
1325 __m256i L_AD12_AD28 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi16(L_AB8_AB24, L_CD8_CD24);
1326 __m256i L_AD8 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_AD8_AD24, L_AD12_AD28, 0x20);
1327 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_AD8);
1328 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_AD16);
1329 __m256i L_AD24 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_AD8_AD24, L_AD12_AD28, 0x31);
1330 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_AD24);
1331 __m256i L_E = lhs.loadPacket(m, k + 4);
1332 __m256i L_F = lhs.loadPacket(m, k + 5);
1333 __m256i L_EF0_EF16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi8(L_E, L_F);
1334 __m256i L_EF8_EF24 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi8(L_E, L_F);
1335 __m256i L_G = lhs.loadPacket(m, k + 6);
1336 __m256i L_H = lhs.loadPacket(m, k + 7);
1337 __m256i L_GH0_GH16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi8(L_G, L_H);
1338 __m256i L_GH8_GH24 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi8(L_G, L_H);
1339 __m256i L_EH0_EH16 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi16(L_EF0_EF16, L_GH0_GH16);
1340 __m256i L_EH4_EH20 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi16(L_EF0_EF16, L_GH0_GH16);
1341 __m256i L_EH0 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_EH0_EH16, L_EH4_EH20, 0x20);
1342 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_EH0);
1343 __m256i L_EH16 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_EH0_EH16, L_EH4_EH20, 0x31);
1344 __m256i L_EH8_EH24 = _mm256_unpacklo_epi16(L_EF8_EF24, L_GH8_GH24);
1345 __m256i L_EH12_EH28 = _mm256_unpackhi_epi16(L_EF8_EF24, L_GH8_GH24);
1346 __m256i L_EH8 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_EH8_EH24, L_EH12_EH28, 0x20);
1347 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_EH8);
1348 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_EH16);
1349 __m256i L_EH24 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(L_EH8_EH24, L_EH12_EH28, 0x31);
1350 _mm256_store_si256(blockA_256++, L_EH24);
1351 }
1352 }
1353}

1355// Arrange a block of the right input matrix in contiguous memory.
1356//
1357// Given column major input (A0 beside A1 in memory):
1358// A0 B0 C0 D0 E0 F0 G0 H0 ...
1359// A1 B1 C1 D1 E1 F1 G1 H1 ...
1360// A2 B2 C2 D2 E2 F2 G2 H2 ...
1361// A3 B3 C3 D3 E3 F3 G3 H3 ...
1362// A4 B4 C4 D4 E4 F4 G4 H4 ...
1363// A5 B5 C5 D5 E5 F5 G5 H5 ...
1364// A6 B6 C6 D6 E6 F6 G6 H6 ...
1365// A7 B7 C7 D7 E7 F7 G7 H7 ...
1366// A8 ...
1367// ...
1368//
1369// Packing yields row major output (A0 beside A1 in memory):
1370// A0 A1 A2 A3 A4 A5 A6 A7
1371// B0 B1 B2 B3 B4 B5 B6 B7
1372// ...
1373//
1374// At least four elements of the same col are arranged contiguously because
1375// maddubs and madd both perform an adjacent addition in the kernel. We can
1376// save work by leaving 8 adjacent elements because kr = 8.
1377template <typename Index, typename DataMapper, int nr, bool Conjugate,
1378 bool PanelMode>
1379struct gemm_pack_rhs<QUInt8, Index, DataMapper, nr, ColMajor, Conjugate,
1380 PanelMode> {
1381 EIGEN_DONT_INLINE void operator()(QUInt8* blockB, const DataMapper& rhs,
1382 Index depth, Index cols, Index stride = 0,
1383 Index offset = 0);
1384};
1385
1386template <typename Index, typename DataMapper, int nr, bool Conjugate,
1387 bool PanelMode>
1388EIGEN_DONT_INLINE void gemm_pack_rhs<QUInt8, Index, DataMapper, nr, ColMajor,
1389 Conjugate, PanelMode>::
1390operator()(QUInt8* blockB, const DataMapper& rhs, Index depth, Index cols,
1391 Index stride, Index offset) {
1392 eigen_assert(stride == 0);
1393 eigen_assert(offset == 0);
1394
1395 // Use alternate function for weird sizes
1396 if (cols % 32 != 0 || depth % 32 != 0) {
1397 gemm_pack_rhs_any<QUInt8, Index, DataMapper, nr, ColMajor, Conjugate, PanelMode> rhs_pack;
1398 return rhs_pack(blockB, rhs, depth, cols, stride, offset);
1399 }
1400
1401 // Get vector pointer
1402 __m256i* blockB_256 = reinterpret_cast<__m256i*>(blockB);
1403
1404 // Perform a step of the packing for 4 columns
1405 __m256i R_AB_L, R_AB_H, R_CD_L, R_CD_H, R_AD_0, R_AD_8, R_AD_16, R_AD_24;
1406#define PACK_STEP \
1407 R_AB_L = _mm256_unpacklo_epi64(R_A, R_B); \
1408 R_CD_L = _mm256_unpacklo_epi64(R_C, R_D); \
1409 R_AB_H = _mm256_unpackhi_epi64(R_A, R_B); \
1410 R_CD_H = _mm256_unpackhi_epi64(R_C, R_D); \
1411 R_AD_0 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(R_AB_L, R_CD_L, 0x20); \
1412 R_AD_16 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(R_AB_L, R_CD_L, 0x31); \
1413 R_AD_8 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(R_AB_H, R_CD_H, 0x20); \
1414 R_AD_24 = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(R_AB_H, R_CD_H, 0x31); \
1415 _mm256_store_si256(blockB_256, R_AD_0); \
1416 _mm256_store_si256(blockB_256 + 8, R_AD_8); \
1417 _mm256_store_si256(blockB_256 + 16, R_AD_16); \
1418 _mm256_store_si256(blockB_256 + 24, R_AD_24); \
1419 blockB_256++;
1420
1421 // Pack cols in sets of 32
1422 for (Index n = 0; n < cols; n += 32) {
1423 // Pack depth in sets of 32
1424 for (Index k = 0; k < depth; k += 32) {
1425 __m256i R_A = rhs.loadPacket(k, n);
1426 __m256i R_B = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 1);
1427 __m256i R_C = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 2);
1428 __m256i R_D = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 3);
1429 PACK_STEP;
1430
1431 R_A = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 4);
1432 R_B = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 5);
1433 R_C = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 6);
1434 R_D = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 7);
1435 PACK_STEP;
1436
1437 R_A = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 8);
1438 R_B = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 9);
1439 R_C = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 10);
1440 R_D = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 11);
1441 PACK_STEP;
1442
1443 R_A = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 12);
1444 R_B = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 13);
1445 R_C = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 14);
1446 R_D = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 15);
1447 PACK_STEP;
1448
1449 R_A = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 16);
1450 R_B = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 17);
1451 R_C = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 18);
1452 R_D = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 19);
1453 PACK_STEP;
1454
1455 R_A = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 20);
1456 R_B = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 21);
1457 R_C = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 22);
1458 R_D = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 23);
1459 PACK_STEP;
1460
1461 R_A = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 24);
1462 R_B = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 25);
1463 R_C = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 26);
1464 R_D = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 27);
1465 PACK_STEP;
1466
1467 R_A = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 28);
1468 R_B = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 29);
1469 R_C = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 30);
1470 R_D = rhs.loadPacket(k, n + 31);
1471 PACK_STEP;
1472
1473 blockB_256 += 24;
1474 }
1475 }
1476#undef PACK_STEP
1477}

1479// Perform the actual multiplication on packed inputs
1480template<typename Index, typename DataMapper, int mr, int nr, bool ConjugateLhs, bool ConjugateRhs>
1481struct gebp_kernel<QInt8, QUInt8, Index, DataMapper, mr, nr, ConjugateLhs, ConjugateRhs>
1482{
1483 typedef typename DataMapper::LinearMapper LinearMapper;
1484
1485 EIGEN_DONT_INLINE
1486 void operator()(const DataMapper& res, const QInt8* blockA, const QUInt8* blockB,
1487 Index rows, Index depth, Index cols, QInt32 alpha,
1488 Index strideA=-1, Index strideB=-1, Index offsetA=0, Index offsetB=0);
1489};
1490
1491template<typename Index, typename DataMapper, int mr, int nr, bool ConjugateLhs, bool ConjugateRhs>
1492EIGEN_DONT_INLINE
1493void gebp_kernel<QInt8, QUInt8, Index, DataMapper, mr, nr, ConjugateLhs, ConjugateRhs>
1494::operator()(const DataMapper& res, const QInt8* blockA, const QUInt8* blockB,
1495 Index rows, Index depth, Index cols, QInt32 alpha,
1496 Index strideA, Index strideB, Index offsetA, Index offsetB)
1497{
1498 EIGEN_STATIC_ASSERT(!ConjugateLhs, YOU_MADE_A_PROGRAMMING_MISTAKE);
1499 EIGEN_STATIC_ASSERT(!ConjugateRhs, YOU_MADE_A_PROGRAMMING_MISTAKE);
1500 eigen_assert(alpha.value == 1);
1501 eigen_assert(strideA == -1);
1502 eigen_assert(strideB == -1);
1503 eigen_assert(offsetA == 0);
1504 eigen_assert(offsetB == 0);
1505 eigen_assert(rows > 0);
1506 eigen_assert(cols > 0);
1507 eigen_assert(depth > 0);
1508 eigen_assert(blockA);
1509 eigen_assert(blockB);
1510
1511 // Use alternate function for weird sizes
1512 if (rows % 32 != 0 || cols % 32 != 0 || depth % 32 != 0) {
1513 gebp_kernel_any<QInt8, QUInt8, Index, DataMapper, mr, nr, ConjugateLhs, ConjugateRhs> gebp;
1514 return gebp(res, blockA, blockB, rows, depth, cols, alpha, strideA, strideB, offsetA, offsetB);
1515 }
1516
1517 // Create result block
1518 QInt32* blockO = aligned_new<QInt32>(32 * 32);
1519 // Allocating the result block is about 5-10% faster than declaring stack
1520 // space. It is unclear why this is the case.
1521 // ei_declare_aligned_stack_constructed_variable(QInt32, blockO, 32 * 32, 0);
1522 memset(blockO, 0, 32 * 32 * sizeof(QInt32));
1523
1524 // Get vectorized pointers
1525 __m256i* blockO_256 = reinterpret_cast<__m256i*>(blockO);
1526 const __m256i* blockA_256 = reinterpret_cast<const __m256i*>(blockA);
1527 const __m256i* blockB_256 = reinterpret_cast<const __m256i*>(blockB);
1528
1529 // Loop over blocks of 32 columns
1530 for (Index n = 0; n < cols; n += 32) {
1531 // Reset index into blockA
1532 Index indexL = 0;
1533 // Loop over blocks of 32 rows
1534 for (Index m = 0; m < rows; m += 32) {
1535 // Reset index into blockB
1536 Index indexR = n / 32 * depth;
1537 // Loop over blocks of 8 on depth
1538 for (Index k = 0; k < depth; k += 8) {
1539 // Load inputs
1540 __m256i L_AD0 = blockA_256[indexL++];
1541 __m256i L_AD8 = blockA_256[indexL++];
1542 __m256i L_AD16 = blockA_256[indexL++];
1543 __m256i L_AD24 = blockA_256[indexL++];
1544 __m256i L_EH0 = blockA_256[indexL++];
1545 __m256i L_EH8 = blockA_256[indexL++];
1546 __m256i L_EH16 = blockA_256[indexL++];
1547 __m256i L_EH24 = blockA_256[indexL++];
1548 __m256i R_AH0 = blockB_256[indexR++];
1549 __m256i R_AH4 = blockB_256[indexR++];
1550 __m256i R_AH8 = blockB_256[indexR++];
1551 __m256i R_AH12 = blockB_256[indexR++];
1552 __m256i R_AH16 = blockB_256[indexR++];
1553 __m256i R_AH20 = blockB_256[indexR++];
1554 __m256i R_AH24 = blockB_256[indexR++];
1555 __m256i R_AH28 = blockB_256[indexR++];
1556
1557 // This constant is used with madd to convert 16 bit to 32 bit
1558 const __m256i ONE = _mm256_set1_epi32(0x00010001);
1559
1560 // Declare variables used in COMPUTE_STEP
1561 __m256i P_16_A, P_16_B, P_32_A, P_32_B, P_32;
1562
1563#define COMPUTE_STEP(R_INPUT_A, R_INPUT_B, OFFSET) \
1564 P_16_A = _mm256_maddubs_epi16(R_INPUT_A, L_AD0); \
1565 P_32_A = _mm256_madd_epi16(P_16_A, ONE); \
1566 P_16_B = _mm256_maddubs_epi16(R_INPUT_B, L_EH0); \
1567 P_32_B = _mm256_madd_epi16(P_16_B, ONE); \
1568 P_32 = _mm256_add_epi32(P_32_A, P_32_B); \
1569 _mm256_store_si256( \
1570 blockO_256 + 4 * OFFSET, \
1571 _mm256_add_epi32(_mm256_load_si256(blockO_256 + 4 * OFFSET), P_32)); \
1572 \
1573 P_16_A = _mm256_maddubs_epi16(R_INPUT_A, L_AD8); \
1574 P_32_A = _mm256_madd_epi16(P_16_A, ONE); \
1575 P_16_B = _mm256_maddubs_epi16(R_INPUT_B, L_EH8); \
1576 P_32_B = _mm256_madd_epi16(P_16_B, ONE); \
1577 P_32 = _mm256_add_epi32(P_32_A, P_32_B); \
1578 _mm256_store_si256( \
1579 blockO_256 + 4 * OFFSET + 1, \
1580 _mm256_add_epi32(_mm256_load_si256(blockO_256 + 4 * OFFSET + 1), P_32)); \
1581 \
1582 P_16_A = _mm256_maddubs_epi16(R_INPUT_A, L_AD16); \
1583 P_32_A = _mm256_madd_epi16(P_16_A, ONE); \
1584 P_16_B = _mm256_maddubs_epi16(R_INPUT_B, L_EH16); \
1585 P_32_B = _mm256_madd_epi16(P_16_B, ONE); \
1586 P_32 = _mm256_add_epi32(P_32_A, P_32_B); \
1587 _mm256_store_si256( \
1588 blockO_256 + 4 * OFFSET + 2, \
1589 _mm256_add_epi32(_mm256_load_si256(blockO_256 + 4 * OFFSET + 2), P_32)); \
1590 \
1591 P_16_A = _mm256_maddubs_epi16(R_INPUT_A, L_AD24); \
1592 P_32_A = _mm256_madd_epi16(P_16_A, ONE); \
1593 P_16_B = _mm256_maddubs_epi16(R_INPUT_B, L_EH24); \
1594 P_32_B = _mm256_madd_epi16(P_16_B, ONE); \
1595 P_32 = _mm256_add_epi32(P_32_A, P_32_B); \
1596 _mm256_store_si256( \
1597 blockO_256 + 4 * OFFSET + 3, \
1598 _mm256_add_epi32(_mm256_load_si256(blockO_256 + 4 * OFFSET + 3), P_32));
1599
1600 // Permute and shuffle to copy a single value across the entire vector
1601 // Then compute the multiplication
1602 __m256i R_AH0_ = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(R_AH0, R_AH0, 0x00);
1603 __m256i R_AD0 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0x00);
1604 __m256i R_EH0 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0x55);
1605 COMPUTE_STEP(R_AD0, R_EH0, 0);
1606 __m256i R_AD1 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0xAA);
1607 __m256i R_EH1 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0xFF);
1608 COMPUTE_STEP(R_AD1, R_EH1, 1);
1609 R_AH0_ = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(R_AH0, R_AH0, 0x11);
1610 __m256i R_AD2 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0x00);
1611 __m256i R_EH2 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0x55);
1612 COMPUTE_STEP(R_AD2, R_EH2, 2);
1613 __m256i R_AD3 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0xAA);
1614 __m256i R_EH3 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0xFF);
1615 COMPUTE_STEP(R_AD3, R_EH3, 3);
1616
1617 R_AH0_ = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(R_AH4, R_AH4, 0x00);
1618 R_AD0 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0x00);
1619 R_EH0 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0x55);
1620 COMPUTE_STEP(R_AD0, R_EH0, 4);
1621 R_AD1 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0xAA);
1622 R_EH1 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0xFF);
1623 COMPUTE_STEP(R_AD1, R_EH1, 5);
1624 R_AH0_ = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(R_AH4, R_AH4, 0x11);
1625 R_AD2 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0x00);
1626 R_EH2 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0x55);
1627 COMPUTE_STEP(R_AD2, R_EH2, 6);
1628 R_AD3 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0xAA);
1629 R_EH3 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0xFF);
1630 COMPUTE_STEP(R_AD3, R_EH3, 7);
1631
1632 R_AH0_ = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(R_AH8, R_AH8, 0x00);
1633 R_AD0 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0x00);
1634 R_EH0 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0x55);
1635 COMPUTE_STEP(R_AD0, R_EH0, 8);
1636 R_AD1 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0xAA);
1637 R_EH1 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0xFF);
1638 COMPUTE_STEP(R_AD1, R_EH1, 9);
1639 R_AH0_ = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(R_AH8, R_AH8, 0x11);
1640 R_AD2 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0x00);
1641 R_EH2 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0x55);
1642 COMPUTE_STEP(R_AD2, R_EH2, 10);
1643 R_AD3 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0xAA);
1644 R_EH3 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0xFF);
1645 COMPUTE_STEP(R_AD3, R_EH3, 11);
1646
1647 R_AH0_ = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(R_AH12, R_AH12, 0x00);
1648 R_AD0 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0x00);
1649 R_EH0 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0x55);
1650 COMPUTE_STEP(R_AD0, R_EH0, 12);
1651 R_AD1 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0xAA);
1652 R_EH1 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0xFF);
1653 COMPUTE_STEP(R_AD1, R_EH1, 13);
1654 R_AH0_ = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(R_AH12, R_AH12, 0x11);
1655 R_AD2 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0x00);
1656 R_EH2 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0x55);
1657 COMPUTE_STEP(R_AD2, R_EH2, 14);
1658 R_AD3 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0xAA);
1659 R_EH3 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0xFF);
1660 COMPUTE_STEP(R_AD3, R_EH3, 15);
1661
1662 R_AH0_ = _mm256_permute2x128_si256(R_AH16, R_AH16, 0x00);
1663 R_AD0 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0x00);
1664 R_EH0 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0x55);
1665 COMPUTE_STEP(R_AD0, R_EH0, 16);

1678 R_AD0 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0x00);

1700 R_AD2 = _mm256_shuffle_epi32(R_AH0_, 0x00);

1723 }

1726 Index i = 0;
1727 for (Index j = n; j < n + 32; j++) {

1729 LinearMapper r1 = res.getLinearMapper(m + 8, j);
